   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rapid Response to nutrition crises</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In addition to HR capacity building, targeted centers are supported with nutritional, anthropometric and medical equipment and supplies as well as financial support to allow for treatment standards as per national protocol. The project targets treatment for 2.500 SAM cases (1.200 male and 1.300 female). Approximately 95% of the beneficiary caseload receive care via OTP established within health centres, while 5% (N=125 persons) are treated for complications at the SC, established at the zone&#x2019;s main reference hospital. AAH covers food and transport for SC patients&#x2019; caregivers to facilitate treatment.</narrative>
  </description>
